# Gmail

This package allows user to read emails from gmail inbox. The current implementation
uses IMAP for reading from gmail server. The default values for hostname when establishing
connection is `imap.gmail.com` and port is `993`.

Example usage:

        from gmail import imap

       conn = imap.connect()
       imap.authenticat(conn, your_username, your_password)
       email_list = imap.get_emails(conn, filters='ALL')

       for mail in email_list:
           print(mail)

filters parameter in `get_emails` uses `search` method from `imaplib`. Lookup valid search parameters
from imaplib documentation
